So I landed Jeb on Bop, saw the squid, planted a flag, etc.  Got him back to the station to level up that and more.  And _nothing_.

I he has been leading to all the new places and crew that has gone to fewer places are Level 5 when he is only 4.

Anybody know what's up?

I check the persistent file, and his most recent stuff is there under Flight Log.

All of your previous flights in the career log have ended with "Recover" or "Die".  Does Jeb need to return to KSC ("Recover") to get credit for all the things he's done in and around Jool?

On 1/3/2020 at 11:58 PM, davidpsummers said:

So I landed Jeb on Bop, saw the squid, planted a flag, etc.  Got him back to the station to level up that and more.  And _nothing_.

Do you have a science lab on the station? Do you have a comnet link to Kerbin? (Not sure if that is needed...) And did you "level up" your crew from the science lab while Jeb was on board the station? (E.g. while in the science lab.)

On 1/3/2020 at 11:58 PM, davidpsummers said:

I'll paste his roster entry below....

There are several item missing in that entry (not in the least the whole block about the EVA parachute), which version of KSP are you running>

A Jeb in one of my career saves was....ejem...lost in mission, let's say. When he respawned, he was never quite the same kerbal. When everybody learns in space and gets experience (I have the option activated), he can only do that after getting a shower at home, thinking about the void he went through. Sad...

I am using version 1.3

I have taken Jeb back to the lab module and hit level up.  No joy.  I haven't taken him back to Kerbin to level up.  I guess that is it?

He is currently out on Laythe.  I have plans for him and it is along trip to Kerbin and back out.  Any suggestions?  Any edits to the persistent file I can do?

Hello,

If you want to hack it, which I don't believe , ... replace the:

Sample:

 11 = Die

to:

 11 = Recover

 

and to the same in all "Die" entries

Cheers!

Rather than just "This" to @pmborg I'll add a link to the bug that causes this to happen. Filed by a very handsome Kerballer.

Bug 13518

I submitted it 3 years ago, and it was confirmed 1 year ago (amusingly, both are in the week of their anniversary right now). But it's not seen any real action.

I found that if I move the items under "Flight_Log" into "Career_Log", then add a "26 = Recover" at the end, he levels up.

I also put into "Flight_Log" a new flight...

"Flight 27

27 = Orbit,Pol"
 

But, of course, that doesn't fix the problem (I have to do that anytime I level up).  I think pmborg's fix is probably better.
